postEnrollmentKeys1._description: Represents an API request to create an enrollment key.
postEnrollmentKeys1._Name_description: Key name, only visible to admins and meant to be used for easy identification.
postEnrollmentKeys1.Name: Howdy
postEnrollmentKeys1._KeyName_description: The unique key name that will be entered by a user to redeem this enrollment key.
postEnrollmentKeys1._DepartmentId_description:
New accounts created with this key will be created in this department.
If not specified, the top-level department for the authenticated user will be used.
See /api/rest/v1/Help/Api/GET-api-Rest-v1-departments_departmentName_externalId for a list of departments.
postEnrollmentKeys1._UsernameType_description:
Specifies how usernames will be generated when new accounts are created using this enrollment key.
If not specified, the Email type will be used.

Possible Enum Values:

`0 = UserInput` `1 = Email` `2 = FirstNameLastName`
postEnrollmentKeys1._MaxUses_description: Maximum times the enrollment key can be used. If you do not send this value or send null for this value the key will have unlimited uses.
postEnrollmentKeys1._StartDate_description: The enrollment key will not be redeemable until this date. If not set, the key is immediately redeemable.
postEnrollmentKeys1._ExpiryDate_description: The enrollment key will not be redeemable after this date. If not set, the key never expires.
postEnrollmentKeys1._LanguageId_description:
The number of the language to be used in the Enrollment Key instructions email.
See /api/rest/v1/languages for a list of languages.
Will default to 1 (English) if not provided.
postEnrollmentKeys1._SendNewUserMessageOnEnrollment_descript: Should a user creating a new account using this enrollment key receive a welcome email? Default is false.
postEnrollmentKeys1._ExternalId_description: When specified, associates the enrollment key with an externally provide identifier.
postEnrollmentKeys1._Courses_description: The courses the user will be enrolled into upon redemption of this enrollment key.
postEnrollmentKeys1._SignupFields_description:
Overrides for the fields the user can fill in to create their new account when using this enrollment key.
The defaults are set on the client and will always be used, but these fields allow some of those behaviours to be overridden.

SignupFields._description: Represents an API request to override an existing field definition Behavior/DefaultValue.
SignupFields._CustomFieldDefinitionId_description: If overriding a Custom Field Definition, this is its unique identifier. Otherwise use 00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000
SignupFields._Name_description: The name of the field, either the Default Field or Custom Field Definition.
SignupFields._Behavior_description:
How this user field behaves when a user is creating a new account.

Possible Enum Values:

`0 = Optional` `1 = Required` `2 = Hidden` `3 = Locked` `4 = ReadOnly`
SignupFields._DefaultValue_description:
The value matching the Type that will be pre-populated in this field when the EnrollmentKey is used to create a new user account.
If this is a Date or DateTime it must be in the ISO-8601 DateTime format with optional milliseconds, e.g.: 2016-11-09T18:22:27.4044323Z

postEnrollmentKeys2._Name_description: Key name, only visible to admins and meant to be used for easy identification.
postEnrollmentKeys2._KeyName_description: The unique key name that will be entered by a user to redeem this enrollment key.

See /api/rest/v1/Help/Api/GET-api-Rest-v1-departments_departmentName_externalId for a list of departments.
postEnrollmentKeys2._UsernameType_description:
The key will create a username for the new user based on this selection.

Possible Enum Values:

`0 = UserInput` `1 = Email` `2 = FirstNameLastName`
postEnrollmentKeys2._MaxUses_description: Maximum times the enrollment key can be used. If you do not send this value or send null for this value the key will have unlimited uses.
postEnrollmentKeys2._StartDate_description: The enrollment key will not be redeemable until this date. If not set, the key is immediately redeemable.
postEnrollmentKeys2._ExpiryDate_description: The enrollment key will not be redeemable after this date. If not set, the key never expires.
postEnrollmentKeys2._LanguageId_description:
The number of the language to be used in the Enrollment Key instructions email.
See /api/rest/v1/languages for a list of languages.
Will default to 1 (English) if not provided.
postEnrollmentKeys2._SendNewUserMessageOnEnrollment_descript: Should a user creating a new account using this enrollment key receive a welcome email? Default is false.
postEnrollmentKeys2._ExternalId_description: Externally provided identifier for this enrollment key.
postEnrollmentKeys2._Courses_description: The courses the user will be enrolled into upon redemption of this enrollment key.
postEnrollmentKeys2._SignupFields_description:
Overrides for the fields the user can fill in to create their new account when using this enrollment key.
The defaults are set on the client and will always be used, but these fields allow some of those behaviours to be overridden.

SignupFields._description: Represents a request to update an existing SignupField.
SignupFields._CustomFieldDefinitionId_description: If overriding a Custom Field Definition, this is its unique identifier. Otherwise use 00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000
SignupFields._Name_description: The name of the field, either the Default Field or Custom Field Definition.
SignupFields._Behavior_description:
How this user field behaves when a user is creating a new account.

Possible Enum Values:

`0 = Optional` `1 = Required` `2 = Hidden` `3 = Locked` `4 = ReadOnly`
SignupFields._DefaultValue_description:
The value matching the Type that will be pre-populated in this field when the EnrollmentKey is used to create a new user account.
If this is a Date or DateTime it must be in the ISO-8601 DateTime format with optional milliseconds, e.g.: 2016-11-09T18:22:27.4044323Z

postEnrollment1._description: Request Model recevied in the body that represents information about a learner's enrollment in a course.
postEnrollment1._status_description:
The enrollment status.

Possible Enum Values:

`0 = NotStarted` `1 = InProgress` `2 = PendingApproval` `3 = Complete` `4 = NotComplete` `5 = Failed` `6 = Declined` `7 = PendingEvaluationRequired` `8 = OnWaitlist` `9 = Absent` `10 = NotApplicable` `11 = PendingProctor` `12 = ReadyForReview`
postEnrollment1._dateCompleted_description: The date the enrollment was completed.
postEnrollment1._courseVersionId_description: Enrollment is for a specific course version.
postEnrollment1._acceptedTermsAndConditions_description: Learner has accepted the terms and conditions.
postEnrollment1._timeSpentTicks_description: The length of time the learner has spent in the course (stored as ticks).
postEnrollment1._dateStarted_description: The date the learner started the course.
postEnrollment1._enrollmentKeyId_description: When present, indicates the enrollment key used to enroll into the course.
postEnrollment1._certificateId_description: When present, indicates the id of the certificate awarded for completing the course.
postEnrollment1._credits_description: When present, indicates the credits accumulated for the course.
postEnrollment1._isActive_description: If true, indicates the enrollment is the current (active) enrollment. false if a historical enrollment.
postEnrollment1._courseCollectionId_description:
This is set if the Course is an Online Course or a Instructor Led Course that was enrolled in via a Course Bundle or Curriculum.
This refers back to the CourseBundle's ID or Curriculum's ID.
postEnrollment1._accessDate_description: Course cannot be started until this date. Does not stop users from enrolling in it, though.
postEnrollment1._dateDue_description: The date the learner must complete the course by.
postEnrollment1._avatar_description: The display path of a User's Avatar.
postEnrollment1._creditTypeCredits_description: The credits awarded by credit type.
